"Mezquita F., Roca J.R., Reed J.M., Wansard G.","Quantifying species-environment relationships in non-marine Ostracoda for ecological and palaeoecological studies: Examples using Iberian data",2005,"Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology","225","1-4",,"93","117",,,10.1016/j.palaeo.2004.02.052,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-24344501362&partnerID=40&md5=f6d64f78b868deaf098fd8fce46a536a","Dep. Microbiologia I Ecologia, Fac. Biologia, Univ. València, E-46100 Burjassot, Spain; Department Geography, Univ. Hull, Kingston-upon-Hull, GB-HU6 7RX, United Kingdom; Dep. de Géologie Fondamentale et Appliquée, Faculté Polytechnique de Mons, 9 rue de Houdain, B-7000 Mons, Belgium","Mezquita, F., Dep. Microbiologia I Ecologia, Fac. Biologia, Univ. València, E-46100 Burjassot, Spain; Roca, J.R., Dep. Microbiologia I Ecologia, Fac. Biologia, Univ. València, E-46100 Burjassot, Spain; Reed, J.M., Department Geography, Univ. Hull, Kingston-upon-Hull, GB-HU6 7RX, United Kingdom; Wansard, G., Dep. de Géologie Fondamentale et Appliquée, Faculté Polytechnique de Mons, 9 rue de Houdain, B-7000 Mons, Belgium","With current concerns over issues such as global warming, the use of palaeoecological data to reconstruct past environments has gained a special significance, but much of the work on ostracod ecology and paleoecology has been qualitative in nature, or on a site-specific rather than integrated, regional basis. Furthermore, ostracod ecological relationships are complex, with each species occupying a multidimensional niche, and a range of statistical techniques can be employed to establish the significance of different environmental variables on species distribution. We employ logistic regression (LR) and canonical correspondence analysis (CCA) to define ostracod species niches and assemblage response to environmental gradients, using a modern dataset of 465 ostracod samples from the eastern Iberian Peninsula. In addition to these ecological analyses, we develop ostracod-based transfer functions for the quantitative reconstruction of past environmental change from a modern regional data-set of non-marine ostracod and limnological data, by means of weighted averaging (WA) regression and calibration. Examples cited are primarily from modern and fossil ostracod samples from Iberian water bodies. Our results suggest that water chemistry (solute composition and concentration) and temperature are the factors to which non-marine ostracod species respond in a more clear and consistent way. Species-environment relationships modelled using the transfer-function approach of WA are strong for the above-mentioned variables, and therefore these models may be of great help in palaeoenvironmental reconstructions. © 2005 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","Ecological indicators; Gradient analysis; Iberian Peninsula; Logistic regression; Ostracoda; Transfer functions","niche; ostracod; paleoecology; paleoenvironment; transfer function; Eastern Hemisphere; Eurasia; Europe; Iberian Peninsula; Southern Europe; World; Ostracoda",,,,,,"Aladin, N.V., Salinity tolerance, morphology and physiology of the osmoregulatory organ in Ostracoda with special reference to Ostracoda from the Aral Sea (1993) Ostracoda in the Earth and Life Sciences, pp. 387-403. , K.G. McKenzie P.J. Jones A.A. Balkema Rotterdam; Allaby, M., (1998) A Dictionary of Ecology, , 2nd ed. Oxford University Press New York; Appelo, C.A.J., Postma, D., (1993) Geochemistry, Groundwater and Pollution, , A. A. Balkema Rotterdam; Austin, M.P., Continuum concept, ordination methods and niche theory (1985) Ann. Rev. Ecolog. Syst., 16, pp. 39-61; Baltanás, A., Montes, C., Martino, P., Distribution patterns of ostracods in Iberian saline lakes. Influence of ecological factors (1990) Hydrobiologia, 197, pp. 207-220; Baltanás, A., Beroiz, B., López, A., (1996) Lista Faunística Y Bibliográfica de Los Ostrácodos No-marinos (Crustacea, Ostracoda) de la Península Ibérica, Islas Baleares e Islas 